headline: DBS Bank and Goldman Sachs Execute First Interbank Crypto Options Trade
summary: Two of the world’s largest financial institutions, DBS Bank and Goldman Sachs (GS), have executed the first-ever over-the-counter (OTC) cryptocurrency options trade between banks, signaling a major step toward integrating digital assets trading into traditional finance. The trade involved cash-settled Bitcoin BTC $110 356 24h volatility: 2.4% Market cap: $2.20 ...

headline: 3 Big Reasons GS Should Be On Your Watchlist
summary: What a fantastic six months it’s been for Goldman Sachs. Shares of the company have skyrocketed 44%, hitting $790.44. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.

headline: Is Goldman Sachs a Good Value After Surging 38% in 2025?
summary: Trying to decide what to do with Goldman Sachs Group shares right now? You are definitely not alone. The stock has been moving in ways that turn heads, whether you are a long-term believer or just dipping your toe in the financial sector. In the past week, shares jumped 4.4%, easily catching the eye after a modest pullback of around 1.3% over the past month.
